Finding Objects That Have Changed

After an operation is performed in View Manager, object differences are indicated by their status classifications. Any object except a server can have differences, and all statuses except Current indicate that differences exist. See Understanding View Manager Status Classifications.

When merging is done automatically, unresolved text files contain conflicts. (For text files, a conflict is defined as a difference between two corresponding lines of two corresponding files.) When merging is not done automatically or by substitution, unresolved text files can contain any type of difference. View Manager includes a merge utility that allows you to resolve conflicts or differences in the files.

For binary files, a conflict is simply as a difference between two corresponding files. Unless you substitute the source or target file as the merged file, all binary files with conflicts are unresolved.

To find object differences:

Do one of the following:

  • Select Find > Next Difference or Find > Previous Difference from the menu bar.

  • Click the Find Next Difference button or the Find Previous Difference button on the toolbar.

See Comparing Files and Resolving Conflicts.
